body:
Two test cases for import.
Test1: I give up. 

iverilog -g2012 test1.sv
```
package MyStd;
    typedef logic [31:0] my_int32;
endpackage

package MyInterfaces;
    import MyStd::*;
    typedef struct packed
    {
        my_int32 data;
    } Response;
endpackage

module testmodule();
    import MyInterfaces::*;
    Response rsp;
initial begin
    rsp = 0;
end
endmodule
```
Test2: Compiles fine.

iverilog -g2012 test2.sv
```
package MyStd;
    typedef logic [31:0] my_int32;
endpackage

package MyInterfaces;
    //import MyStd::*;
    typedef struct packed
    {
        MyStd::my_int32 data;
    } Response;
endpackage

module testmodule();
    import MyInterfaces::*;
    MyInterfaces::Response rsp;
initial begin
    rsp = 0;
end
endmodule
```

